<Content>We loved it! I booked this Hotel after reading the reviews on this site.....so thought I best put my review on here for future guests!Booked for a visit by myself and my Mum for her birthday. We arrived late Saturday afternoon. Welcomed by a fluent English speaking lady who offered us help with our luggage and then brought us some cold white wine!We went out for dinner that evening, were offered an umbrella and told we could return at any hour, someone would be there to let us in.Slept well on what we both considered clean and comfortable beds....I personally prefer two pillows, but that is being picky!Showered well in a smallish but clean bathroom (but then we ain't two fat ladies, who complain about shower cubicle sizes!)Felipe brought us breakfast which we took on the terrace Sunday morning to the sound of the birds in the cage.On our final day the hotel stored our luggage for us all day which meant we could get our last minute gifts and clothes and tapas without hauling our bags everywhere.The one suggestion I have for improvement would be....please get a kettle to boil your water for tea!! The water heated in the microwave was not hot enough.......I know, typical English moaning about their tea in Spain.....it's just a suggestion!Oh and another thing, which the hotel can do absolutely nothing about....breakfast on Sat/Sun fab, listening to the birds.....breakfast on weekdays, noisy screaming kids from the school at the back!!We loved it though and would return/recommend. 
