<Author>GwenInCal
<Content>Not your average hotel! But nice! We stayed at the L'Antic Espai before we left on a cruise from Barcelona. We stayed in room 107...with access to the terrace.Booking was very easy...we reserved the room through the hotel's website.Location...great! We walked most places, except to Camp Nou...we used the metro...Passaig Gracia stop is a block or so away. The hotel managers gave us a great recommendation for dinner...wonderful tapas...the bread alone was worth going back for. I believe the place (within walking distance of the hotel) was the Ciutat Comtel. We also walked to Las Ramblas and, actually, all the way to Barceloneta (that's a longer walk). A taxi stand is just outside the hotel on the corner, so that was handy when we came into the city from the airport and left to go to the Barcelona port.Room...Bed was super comfortable...which was surprising cause they didn't look very comfortable. Loved the antiques...and the robes! The room was small, but was fine for the two of us...if there were three of us it might have been too cramped. Bathroom...tiny, but very clean. Loved the light switches!Terrace...nice...though we only used it once to enjoy our welcome drink from the managers. The terrace is shared with a couple other rooms, but that wasn't a problem for us...but something someone booking the rooms should know. I know other people were in the hotel, but we didn't hear them...even when they were on the terrace having breakfast. (It's an older building so I thought we'd actually hear everything...maybe it's the way our room was situated...I don't know...but it was pretty quiet.)Service...we were able to use their internet, which was really handy...the maid service was prompt and really cleaned our room up nicely...check in and check out was great. The managers gave us great restaurant recommendations.Elevators...there aren't any (at least I didn't see/use any) and the hotel is on the second (or third?) floor...wasn't a problem for us...(especially since they came down and brought up our bags for us)...but it might be a consideration for others.Food...can't comment on the food, since we didn't have breakfast at the hotel. We asked about a cafe...there are several breakfast cafes within a couple of blocks.I noticed that someone said that there was similarly priced, 4-star hotels on the same road who probably offered amenities that the L'Antic Espai didn't. But we really enjoyed the L'Antic Espai...it was something different for us and was fun for our first visit to Barcelona. 
