<Author>coolcat
<Content>Decent but not fantastic PROSExcellent location! Lovely area from which we walked to the area of Gracia as well as the beach. The area felt safe at night. Close to three metro stations, lots of restaurants etc.It was a treat to live in an apartment building instead of an ordinary hotel. We really liked the tiled floors 鈥?they gave the hotel a very warm and homey feeling.Very clean and tidy! The room was well kept during our stay and smelled fresh and clean.Friendly staff! Both those who spoke excellent English, such as Felipe, and the ladies who spoke less English were very nice. It was not a problem at all to be buzzed in 24/7! They also let us leave our bags in the reception area for a few hours on the day of our departure which we appreciated.Lovely-looking terrace with flowers and bird cages. If you travelled with friends and occupied all 4 rooms facing the terrace it would have been absolutely perfect!CONSAlthough the terrace looks very nice, it just might be a little bit awkward to dress/undress, or take a nap before going out at night, with strangers staring right at you only meters from your bed. Literally! Pictures we had seen mislead us to believe that each room had its own little table with chairs right outside 鈥?instead there were two sitting areas and thus, when they were user by other guests, or staff for that matter (upon arrival there was a man working on some picture frames out there, smoking cigarettes), you had absolutely no privacy in your room unless you kept the heavy curtains closed. Although it was permitted, luckily the other guests were not smoking cigarettes!The mattress was quite firm but not too bad, but the pillow was close to a sack of cement. The blanket that we found in the wardrobe and used on top of the bed sheet could use a wash since it was rather full of stains - though if previous guests had folded it and put it back we can see how this could have been overlooked by the maintenance staff.Water pressure was really bad 鈥?more like a drizzle than pressure 鈥?I had to wash my hair in the sink.The air con worked most of the time, but the last night we had to keep the door open to the terrace that we shared. However, we did not feel very comfortable with this and closed the door again after an hour or so.Doors seemed to be paper thin and since you would be able to hear a whisper in the hallway you can imagine what hollering pre-adolescent boys sounded like shouting and slamming doors. (Loud children are not the hotel's fault of course, but just to give you a picture...) The room was smaller than we expected. Or at least it seemed small due to the placement of the furniture, one double and one single bed. We are average size people and we seemed to constantly be in each others way while moving around the room. It would certainly be very crowded with three people staying together. We stayed here three nights in October, and in short we pretty much agree with everything 鈥渂rabb鈥?said on Oct 5 about the hotel in his review (which we found honest and really not overly critical.). We know this is not a 5 star hotel, but it was still not quite what we expected based on reviews we had read here on TA. 
