<Author>jasiPhilaPa
<Content>A Wonderful Stay My husband and I spent 4 nights at this wonderul Hostal. Upon arriving we were greeted with a complimentry glass of Cava by one of the staff. We stayed in room 102 which was on the street side with an enclosed terrace. When the sound proof doors were closed to the terrace we could not hear any street noise.Occasionally you can hear noise in the hall,but this is to be expected when staying in an old building with character. The Hostal is filled with beautiful antiques. Sergio,the owner is very helpful in recommending restaurants ,he sent us to 2 excellent restaurants. We opted not to have breakfast there as there are wonderful French pastry shops down the street. We did order coffee and this was not very good but served eloquently. In the evening we asked if they had a glass of sherry that we could purchase. They had it indeed and brought it to our room served in beautiful cordial glasses. The location is in walking distance of all the major sites. There is no lift and the Hostal is up one flight of stairs. If you need assistance with your bags the staff will help.I would highly recommend this hotel to people who have an appreciation for antiques and old world charm. If you are looking for a generic hotel this is not for you. As far as the staff goes, they are very friendly,you just have to ask them for what you want.Barcelona is a beautiful city and when I return I will stay at Hostal L'Antic Espai 
