<Author>brabb
<Content>Over-rated I've just returned from a short break with my wife at Hostal L'Antic Espai, which I booked direct after viewing the reviews on this site. I have to say I was disappointed.So, starting at the top, the good stuff:- good location- well equipped room (hairdryer, TV (terrestrial only though) bathrobes etc- aircon- a nice enclosed patio area which rooms 104-107 share- not your usual 'formula' hotel - though the Catalan antiques and bric-a-brac with which the hotel is stuffed leave me cold, I can see that they would be of interest to othersNow lets start gently downhill ...- It is a bit noisy, even if you're in an inside room; though to be honest no more than I'd have expected given the location and architecture- Earlier reviews have mentioned two male staff (one was the owner?) who seem to have looked after guests extremely well - this seems to be the basis on which several 5* reviews have been made. We never saw these - our experience was a series of young women (5 in total over 2 days?). Their English varied from fluent to non-existent. All were charming and tried to be helpful if asked. However, pro-active they were not! For instance:~ Don't expect your luggage to be carried up for you as earlier reporters had (though to be honest this wasn't a big deal, it's only 1 floor up and if you're infirm or have lots of luggage I would really not recommend this place anyway). ~ We were aware from the website, and from a notice in the bathroom saying that breakfasts had to be pre-ordered the night before, that breakfast was available - but it was not mentioned to us once by the staff and we saw no other information about it at all. We went out for breakfast on both days.~ Not once were we asked if everything was OK with the room or if they could help us with anything (day 1 on the hotel receptionist's training course, I'd have thought!)- Although the hotel claims that the booking process is secure, it isn't (take it from me - I work in IT). I crossed my fingers and used it however. And then they sent me a confirmation email with all my cc details there in plain text! If I were booking to stay there again (which I won't) I'd go through one of the booking agencies just to be safe.Full speed now, almost at the bottom!- The shower cubicles are small (particularly to US eyes!) as previous reviewers have mentioned. If that were all I wouldn't have been too bothered. However, on our second and final morning (a Sunday, maybe that was something to do with it?) there was no hot water. So, we had no showers that morning. - Worst of all was the bed.Firstly our bed (and all the doubles as far as I can gather) was only 6' x 4'6 in size. If you're tallish like me or used to sleeping in a larger bed at home this isn't ideal. At least ours had a divan end so I could sleep with my toes out of the bottom. The only other room I was able to look at (104) the bed had a railled end so this wouldn't be possible there...Much worse however was the fact that the mattress was very tired (the owner seems to have bought foam mattresses rather than sprung ones and a year or so after the hotel opened they are badly worn). I woke up the first morning with back-ache - not something I tend to suffer from normally! My wife also commented on the poor mattress (though being much lighter than me she hadn't suffered as much). The second night I slept in the single bed which was also in our room, leaving my wife to the double bed on her own. This was better, but again a foam mattress and it sloped down at one side (perhaps a result of the mattress never having been turned?); so, again not a good night.To my mind, if a hotel can't get the basics right (bed, shower) you have to conclude that it's not worth staying there.So, please excuse this rant. I have tried to be objective but at the end of the day this hotel, which has had some very good reviews in the months after it opened, was a real disappointment for me and I can't recommend it now. 
