<Content>Cozy, cute, and quirky L'Antic Espai was a charming stay in awesome Barcelona. The room I had was small but completely sufficient and decorated beautifully. I used their online reservation and was offered a discounted rate which was honoured when I arrived. Location is quite central with the closet metro station about 2 blocks away and Las Ramblas not more than 5-10min as well. You're right on Gran Via with lots of places to eat/drink very nearby. There is also a supermarket just about across the street to stock up on necessities like water, drinks, snacks, etc.I arrived at 10pm from the airport by taxi and in the dark, the hotel sign was a bit hard to spot. What makes it a bit harder is the huge dark door that's locked... you have to use the intercom to buzz in, so don't expect a big bright hotel lobby. Once you're in, you make your way up the grand staircase (motion detection lights were handy). The atmosphere, once inside, is very warm and homey, is the best way to describe. The lady who checked me in was super nice and was the best welcome to Barcelona at 10pm. Even after checking into my room, I was hungry and she gave me a great recommendation on where to find some tapas and wine. Super helpful!The one minor quirk was, although the wi-fi was free, the security password did not work and I ended up surfing on an unsecured line of an unknown source. Not an issue at all for me, and I did not bring up with the staff, but something they might want to fix if they happen to read this. 
