<Author>Rumpleteazer
<Content>Exquisite and tasteful We stayed 2 nights at L'Antic Espai and I wish we stayed more! Excellent location, near the busy Rambla district and great places to dine, but at the same time in a nice residential area. Very few rooms, each one differs from others in design...wonderful common area decorated in the style of the belle epoque, with antic furniture, porcelain pictures in frames on the walls, and porcelain figures and vases everywhere..two canarys in a cage in the patio...The rooms also have antic design, a good addition to it being an LCD-screen TV with a DVD player attached to it (have you seen many of them in 2-star properties?) Our room also pleasantly surprised us with a large balcony where my friend had her evening cigarette, and an air conditioner which was unnoticeable (no strong blowing from anywhere) but kept the right climate in the room. And, finally, although the room faced a lively street, it was sound proof. We didn't hear any noise at all. Yes, the hotel is located on the 1st floor of a residential building, but we were helped with the luggage on both our arrival and departure so had no problem on that side.Another truth is, that the shower cabin can, in a way, nourish your claustrofobia, but the bathroom itself was of a reasonable size, spotless, and had everything necessary, including a hair dryer. A computer with Internet access available in the common area free of charge added to the overall positive impression. All in all, if you are looking for a faceless standard N-star chain hotel, then look another way. We are going to return. 
