<Content>Unique experience We were visiting Barcelona to celebrate our 30th wedding anniversary and were looking for a hotel which would make the visit more memorable. After reading tripadvisor reviews we had no hesitation in booking 3 nights at the Antic Espai. Booking online was easy and reassuring as we discussed with Sergio the best room for our requirements (quiet).The entrance from the road is unusual as there is an intercom system which allows access to the hotel on the first floor which was well advised in previous reviews. Any anxieties were immediately dispelled when entering the hotel which is beautifully decorated with antique furniture and porcelain.We stayed in room 104 which had a double and single bed which did restrict floor space a little but we knew that when booking. The reason we chose this room was that it was one of four which opened onto a beautiful terrace, perfect for early evening drinks before hitting town. The bathroom was small but well equipped and spotlessly clean as was the room. The hotel location, for us was absolutely perfect, 10 mins walk from Placa de Catalunya where all the buses stopped, including the Aerobus direct from/to the airport and where La Rambla started. The staff were very pleasant and helpful with great advice on local dining. Special mention to Abel, who on discovering it was our anniversary, appeared with a chilled bottle of cava and joined us on the terrace to celebrate.We were looking for a hotel which would add to the Barcelona experience and one which in a few years time we would still remember for the right reasons and Antic Espai fulfilled our wishes as it is truly a unique hotel in a fantastic city. 
