<Author>cmania
<Content>Excellent stay at L'Antic Espai!!!! Hello, I am a travel agent from Virginia and took a small group of 8 ladies to Barcelona for a 5 night stay at the L'Antic Espai. We had a wonderful stay there. We liked the fact the hotel was not directly on Las Ramblas or the busier streets of Barcelona. Yet, it was close to restaurants, cafes, metro, Plaza Cataluna, and Las ramblas. The bathrooms, particularly the showers, were on the small side as was previously mentioned in the reviews, but we made it work. The bathrooms were efficient, clean and we were so anxious to hit the streets and see this beautiful city that it was absolutely no problem making it work. I recommend booking a room that goes out to the lovely terrace. It was a great place to have a glass of cava or wine in the afternoon or evening. However, the main reason I would recommend this hotel and would personally stay there again when I return to Barcelona is the incredible staff of Hostal L'Antic Espai. Abel, Sergio, Felipe and all the staff made our stay memorable!! They always took the time to make excellent recommendations to us and they were absolutely wonderful and helpful in every way. It was great chatting with them and sharing our daily adventures with them. If you want wireless service for your Internet, huge bathrooms with soaking tubs, a restaurant at the hotel, amenities of a 5 star hotel, this place is not for you. Go to a 4-5 star property. But if you are looking for a unique small charming hotel, with a great location and the best staff I have ever found at a hotel, this place is for you. I had several very discerning travelers that were with me on this trip and they absolutely loved this entire experience. Thanks Abel, Sergio, Felipe and the rest of the staff!!! I miss all of you!!!!!Ciao,Anne Walsh 
