<Content>A home in Barcelona! I am always late with the reviews I write, but I wanted to add my comments here as we had a lovely stay at this hotel. Firstly, I should warn visitors that they should consider this less a hotel to visit and more a chance to live in part of an apartment in Barcelona. The entrance is via an unassuming door and you climb the stairs to the entrance which is lovely, for being unexpected. Myself and my husband felt like we were living in Barcelona for the weekend rather than staying in a hotel.The staff on reception were always warm and friendly and their English was always far better than our Spanish (I confess that my poor language abilities in Spain, mean I am grateful for finding that they have made the effort so we can communicate, when my contribution is limited to asking for two beers!The location was also great, we walked for most of the time, or took the tourist bus, which was very handy for getting around.We didn't eat breakfast in the hotel, as it was pricey, we tended to wander to a cafe up the street a little. However, we did have a few drinks on the patio, which was lovely.The room (107) was filled with lovely antiques, and as we don't tend to spend much time in the hotel, the size was fine. The small seating area was nice to have and relax when we were in the room, and of course we could always sit on the patio, with the birds.It was a little noisy in the room, but not as bad as we expected as we were on the main road. The only think I would say, is that I could also feel the metro as it passed underneath.We have already recommended this hotel to friends and would do so again happily. It's a lovely, friendly home from home. Don't expect it to be like a Hilton, it's not, and that is why it is so charming. 
