<Author>WrldTravlr247
<Content>Exceeded our Expectations! After reading all the positive reviews, my friends and I decided to stay at the Hostal L'Antic Espai in Barcelona, Spain. There were a few outweighing factors that assisted in making our decision: 1) Recommendations - As I mentioned, the place had received countless positive reviews and the hotel did fit the bill, by exceeding our expectations. 2) Location - The Hotel is conveniently located a few blocks from plenty of shopping stores and is approximately a 10 walking distance from Las Ramblas. There is a Metro stop approximately two blocks away and many historical sites and museums are within walking distance. 3) Price - In comparing prices to neighboring hotels, the price per night (for a triple bed) totalled approximately 144 (USD) 14, whereas other hotels charged as much as 400+ per night. The staff namely Sergio, Felipe, and Abel were extremely helpful and on numerous occasions went out of their way to feel guests feel welcomed. I personally goofed on our reservations a few times, which caused them to make several changes to our reservations and during each correspondence they warmly made my changes. The rooms are fashionably decorated (much like the staff) and offer a warm welcome. The terrace is a good spot to enjoy the weather while reading a book. You will be able to hear children laughing and playing as the Hotel lies near a school, but they cannot be heard once the doors are shut.Some both positive and not so positive remarks: positive: 1) The staff is super friendly and offers their advice when possible 2) Location - Close to restaurants, shopping, and attraction sites 3) Price - We couldn't find a hotel that offered the same rates where service was unparalleled 4) Free Internet (this helps out and if you'd like there are two Internet cafes nearby) negative: 1) the rooms are somewhat smaller than I was used to, but we managed without any complications 2) During the day you may be able to hear the kitchen a bit, but some earplugs (recommended for every travel) will easily solve the problem. Many more positives for the hotel and highly recommended. This was my second time in Barcelona and I have stayed in approximately five different hotels, but this one was by far the best. 
